<div class="content-data"><div id="list-content-mobile" class="hidden-md hidden-lg"></div><div class="lesson-tab" role="tabpanel"><ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist"><li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#about" aria-controls="about" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Course details</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#transcript" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Transcript</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#pattern" aria-controls="pattern" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Pattern</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#diploma" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Diploma</a></li><li role="presentation"><a class="faq-tab blank" href="#faq" aria-controls="faq" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">FAQs</a></li></ul><div class="tab-content"><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="about"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><div class="demo-slider"><h4 class="text-center">Garments you can make using this technology:</h4><div id="amazingcarousel-container"><div id="amazingcarousel" style="display:none"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-wrapper"><ul class="amazingcarousel-list"><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2045.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2089.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2089.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2147.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/NEW_2147.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li></ul></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>Features:</strong></p><p>The most distinguished feature of this corset is the scalloped edges in the neckline and the bottom.</p><p>There were several reasons, which motivated me to prepare this course:</p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;large number of orders for such corsets.</p><p>2. the unwillingness of the clients to adequately pay for the extra laborious work of making the scalloped corset. Therefore, in this course I will teach you a simple, an easy and yet a fast technique to sew the corset with scalloped edges and at the same times a technique that helps to achieve the desired result.</p><p>The use of my technique will turn the sewing of such complex corset into the budget option, which will be beneficial for you and your client!</p><p><strong>Where to use:</strong></p><ul><li>Perfect for sewing wedding dresses&nbsp;or evening garments;</li><li>Garments made with&nbsp;this technology are suitable for any body type and size;</li><li>Great for reshaping silhouettes and creating proportional forms.</li></ul><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;4h 30m</p></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-9-stitching-bones-to-the-front-central-piece/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-9-stitching-bones-to-the-front-central-piece/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-01-03T18:47:50+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2019-01-03T18:47:50+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2019"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 9. Stitching bones to the front central piece."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 9. Stitching bones to the front central piece."><meta itemprop="description" content="I press the front of the corset lining using the press-form. I stretch it, tighten it and make a rounded shape of the cup. Iron only with a steam generator!"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Fantasy Corset"><meta itemprop="keywords" content="fantasy corset, video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><p><strong>Tutorial 9. Stitching bones to the front central piece. </strong></p><p><strong>I press the front of the corset lining using the press-form. </strong>I stretch it, tighten it and make a rounded shape of the cup. Iron only with a steam generator!</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image147.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image148.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image149.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image150.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image151.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>During pressing I try to stretch fabric toward the side cuts, </strong>so the cut line is relatively straight.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image152.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I stitch the horizontal bone in the bottom of the cup with two parallel stitches. </strong>I use the narrow Rigilene bone, gather it and make it rounded. The ends of bone are placed under the rounded perimeter bone sewn in one side.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image153.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image154.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image155.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image156.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image157.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image158.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I stitch the gathered narrow Rigilene bones in the vertical curves of the corset. </strong>The bones are attached with two parallel stitches and the upper tip is covered with a paint tape.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image159.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image160.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image161.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image162.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I stitch the bones along the second vertical curve. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image163.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image164.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image165.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image166.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Similarly I attach the vertical bones in the front middle pieces with two parallel stitches in accordance with the bone marking. </strong>I use the narrow Rigilene bones.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image167.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image168.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image169.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image170.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I attach the vertical bone to the second middle piece of the front lining. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image171.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image172.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/transcripts/Tutorial%209.files/image173.jpg" alt=""></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format.</p><p>To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose “<strong>PRINT IN ACTUAL SIZE</strong>“.</p><p>The pattern is divided to A4 paper sheets for home printer.</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fantasy_corset/pattern-fantazia.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Fantasy Corset Pattern</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></di